ally syndicated “glenn beck program” — broadcast just outside dallas in las colinas texas — and harvest right told insidesources the second spot will continue airing coast to coast on every station carrying the conservative talk show “we felt like their core values matched our product” operations manager matt neville said of paul and beck specifically praising their emphasis on financial responsibility and saving up for the future neville said harvest right freeze dryers can keep food preserved for  years equipping americans for everything from job loss to economic or natural disasters “it’s not a doomsday endoftheworld thing” he stressed “it’s more about prudent living” should doomsday come however paul said in his ad that harvest right “might just save your lives” this isn’t the first time the company has advertised with glenn beck his television network the blaze has pitched the business repeatedly in live commercials complete with product demonstrations that evoke the home shopping network these spots are central to the conservative media mogul’s plan to transform television advertisements outlined in a  interview with financing services firm btig beck explained how after each segment of his program the camera pulls back to a separate set high above the stage where he and his cohosts sit they remain visible in the background while onair sales talent makes pitches and a small countdown clock shows the remaining time before beck returns compared to traditional ads the approach has been remarkably effective “it’s the stupidest thing you’ve ever seen in your life but nobody turns the channel and they actually watch the commercial because it’s now part of the show” beck said key to this strategy is hiring men and women who look like average americans not “the beautiful people from hollywood” “they’re normal people” beck said “as long as they’re not fake as long as they’re genuine and they can put some things in from their lives people see them as real” acknowledging that not all ads can be product demonstrations the mogul said he planned to send camera crews out to find the stories that make companies like harvest right unique and relay those to his audience follow graham on twitter about the author graham vyse graham vyse is a reporter for insidesources he was previously a staff writer for washington dcs current newspapers where he appeared on the fix’s  list of best state political reporters in the washington post his work has also been published by the post slate and nbc news born and raised in rhode island graham received a masters degree in journalism and public affairs from american university in  he was awarded a paul miller washington reporting fellowship at the national press foundation in  more from inside sources is opinions politics fake fake news read more is opinions politics not a good look in hawaii read more news politics why pirates are better than ninjas a conversation with r… read more is opinions politics ‘sgt pepper’ the creative capitalist read more badintense the ron paul ad is also airing on the gcn network and now alex jones is also doing voice work for the product guy fawkes the ron paul spot was also on rush limbaugh a few minutes ago pm i bought one works great i recommend percy rand paul should shut up about grown men’s work and join his old dad and glen beck peddling some crackpot food freezing machine to tv questquest if ron paul said “it may save lives”……………… then he is not wrong who is going to try to argue with dr paul he is always right questquest the reporter looks gay just saying news energy hidden feed environmental impact statements are front and center of pipeline fights–what is an eis by erin mundahl on july   governmental acronyms particularly military ones are all too often unpronounceable strings of letters forming an… read more is opinions politics a gi bill for the st century by reps kevin mccarthy and phil roe on july   app developer robotics technician digital animator and advanc